name: mortality-surveillance-for-highly-pathogenic-avian-influenza-hpai-at-kulm-wetland-manageme-aa380
notes: Proposal for 20102011 mortality surveillance for Highly Pathogenic Avian Influenza HPAI at Kulm Wetland Management District in North Dakota. Surveillance will focus on priority species known to be sensitive to HPAI. Mortality surveys will be focused on designated routes of 11 Waterfowl Production Areas, which have high known concentrations of the sensitive species. Surveillance will be conducted via ATV or footbased observation surveys along wetlands on a weekly basis from roughly 15 April 2010 iceout through 7 November 2010 freezeup during the migration and throughout the breeding season. Monitoring efforts will continue during the following spring migration, from roughly 131 March. Eleven sites included during the 2007  2009 HPAI monitoring will again be surveyed in 2010. In addition, 35 large wetlands semipermanent wetlands or permanent lakes will be included for the 2010 field season due to the relative proximity to poultry production facilities in eastern Dickey County. Wetlands on private lands in which permission cannot be obtained will be scanned with a spotting scope or binoculars from the nearest road. Moribund avian carcasses obtained during mortality surveillance efforts will be collected, properly packaged, and shipped to the National Wildlife Health Center in Madison, WI following appropriate protocols for causeofdeath determination.  This proposal contains a summary of 20092010 surveillance.
